y Scouts]]\n| NHL\n| 75\n| 5\n| 33\n| 38\n| 82\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | NHL totals\n! 838\n! 68\n! 299\n! 367\n! 1249\n! 21\n! 0\n! 5\n! 5\n! 20\n|}\n\n===International===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:50em\"\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! Year\n! Team\n! Event\n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! GP\n! G\n! A\n! Pts\n! PIM\n|-\n| [[1972 Summit Series|1972]]\n| [[Canada men's national ice hockey team|Canada]]\n| SS\n| 8\n| 0\n| 3\n| 3\n| 13\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*{{icehockeystats|legends=11982}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080126094310/http://www.cshof.ca/hm_profile.php?i=399 Gary Bergman's  biography] at [https://web.archive.org/web/20120209135501/http://www.cshof.ca/index.php Canadian Sports Hall of Fame]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20111002142647/http://www.mbhockeyhalloffame.ca/honoured/players.html?category=9&id=50 Gary Bergman\u2019s biography] at [https://web.archive.org/web/20141004060054/http://www.mbhockeyhalloffame.ca/index.html Manitoba Hockey Hall of Fame]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box | before = [[Gordon Berenson|Red Berenson]] | title = [[Detroit Red Wings#Team captains|Detroit Red Wings captain]] | years = [[1973\u201374 NHL season|1973\u201374]] | after = [[Ted Harris (ice hockey)|Ted Harris]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bergman, Gary}}\n[[Category:1938 births]]\n[[Category:2000 deaths]]\n[[Category:Buffalo Bisons (AHL) players]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey defencemen]]\n[[Category:Cleveland Barons (1937\u20131973) players]]\n[[Category:Detroit Red Wings players]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey people from Ontario]]\n[[Category:Kansas City Scouts players]]\n[[Category:Minnesota North Stars players]]\n[[Category:Quebec Aces (AHL) players]]\n[[Category:Springfield Indians players]]\n[[Category:Winnipeg Braves players]]\n[[Category:Winnipeg Warriors (minor pro) players]]\n[[Category:Sportspe